codec_lzma: take the LZMA SDK header from the system under CHDR_SYSTEM_LZMA

Companion to patch 0001. src/codec_lzma.h unconditionally includes the
vendored copy's header by relative path
("../deps/lzma-25.01/include/LzmaDec.h"), which would defeat
WITH_SYSTEM_LZMA: the vendored header is a shim that #define-renames
every public LzmaDec entry point to a CHDR_-prefixed alias (its first
~15 lines, e.g. LzmaDec_DecodeToBuf -> CHDR_LzmaDec_DecodeToBuf) so the
bundled static copy cannot collide with a real SDK elsewhere in a host
process -- compiling against it produces CHDR_* references that no
system liblzma-sdk exports.

Fixed byte-for-byte on the codec_zstd.h:6-10 pattern (the maintainer's
own solution to the identical problem for zstd): the CHDR_SYSTEM_LZMA
compile definition -- set only by patch 0001's system branch -- selects
a plain #include <LzmaDec.h>, which resolves via lzma-sdk.pc's include
path (-I.../include/lzma-sdk); LzmaDec.h's own quoted #include
"7zTypes.h" then resolves same-directory beside it. The bundled default
build still takes the vendored path, untouched, in the #else. The
translation unit itself needs no changes: libchdr_codec_lzma.c uses
only plain 7-Zip names (LzmaDec_Construct/Allocate/Init/DecodeToBuf/
Free, CLzmaDec, ISzAlloc/ISzAllocPtr, SRes, SizeT, ELzmaStatus,
LZMA_PROPS_SIZE, SZ_OK, LZMA_FINISH_END,
LZMA_STATUS_MAYBE_FINISHED_WITHOUT_MARK -- checked, every one), all
declared by the real SDK's LzmaDec.h/7zTypes.h; the CHDR_ renaming
lives only in the vendored shim this bypasses.

Upstream status: follows the maintainer's own WITH_SYSTEM_* pattern
(added "for distros" per CHANGELOG); candidate for upstreaming, not yet
sent.

diff --git a/src/codec_lzma.h b/src/codec_lzma.h
--- a/src/codec_lzma.h
+++ b/src/codec_lzma.h
@@ -3,7 +3,11 @@
 
 #include <stdint.h>
 
+#ifdef CHDR_SYSTEM_LZMA
+#include <LzmaDec.h>
+#else
 #include "../deps/lzma-25.01/include/LzmaDec.h"
+#endif
 
 #include "../include/libchdr/chd.h"
 
